                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.749,
                                "byte_start": 85353,
                                "byte_stop": 124432,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in NO. 01-1325 Brown versus Legal Foundation of Washington will be announced by Justice Stevens."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.749,
                        "stop": 251.533,
                        "byte_start": 124432,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15060,
                            "name": "John Paul Stevens",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/john_paul_stevens",
                            "last_name": "Stevens",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2704,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 188200800,
                                    "date_end": 1277787600,
                                    "appointing_president": "Gerald Ford",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2704"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32732,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 62101,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/john_paul_stevens.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 12611,
                            "identifier": "john_paul_stevens"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.749,
                                "stop": 17.81,
                                "byte_start": 124432,
                                "byte_stop": 156615,
                                "text": "In the course of their legal practice, attorneys are frequently required to hold clients funds various lengths of time."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 17.81,
                                "stop": 23.442,
                                "byte_start": 156615,
                                "byte_stop": 179185,
                                "text": "They have a professional obligation to avoid commingling their client\u0027s money with their own."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 23.442,
                                "stop": 29.664,
                                "byte_start": 179185,
                                "byte_stop": 204053,
                                "text": "But it is not unethical to pull several client\u0027s fund in a single trust account."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.664,
                                "stop": 50.426,
                                "byte_start": 204053,
                                "byte_stop": 287123,
                                "text": "Before 1980, client funds were typically held in non-interest bearing federal insured checking accounts, but because the federal banking regulations in effect since the great depression prohibited banks from paying interests on checking accounts the value of the use of the client\u0027s money in such accounts innured to the banking institution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.426,
                                "stop": 60.335,
                                "byte_start": 287123,
                                "byte_stop": 326724,
                                "text": "In 1980 Congress authorized federally insured banks to pay interest on a limited category of demand deposit referred to as NOW accounts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 60.335,
                                "stop": 78.918,
                                "byte_start": 326724,
                                "byte_stop": 401121,
                                "text": "This category includes deposits made by individuals and charitable organizations but does include those made by for profit corporations or partnerships, unless the deposits are made pursuant to a program under which charitable organizations have the inclusive right to the interest."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.918,
                                "stop": 86.148,
                                "byte_start": 401121,
                                "byte_stop": 429960,
                                "text": "In response to the change in federal law, every State in the Nation has adapted a so-called IOLTA program."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 86.148,
                                "stop": 92.52,
                                "byte_start": 429960,
                                "byte_stop": 455456,
                                "text": "IOLTA is an acronym for Interest On Lawyers Trust Accounts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.52,
                                "stop": 102.461,
                                "byte_start": 455456,
                                "byte_stop": 495266,
                                "text": "Authorizing the use of NOW accounts for the deposit of client funds and providing that all the interest on such accounts be used for charitable purposes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.461,
                                "stop": 112.138,
                                "byte_start": 495266,
                                "byte_stop": 533928,
                                "text": "This case presents a challenge to the constitutionality of the IOLTA program adopted by the State of Washington Supreme Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.138,
                                "stop": 124.626,
                                "byte_start": 533928,
                                "byte_stop": 583874,
                                "text": "An important feature of that program is that it categorically prohibits deposits of client funds into IOLTA accounts if those funds could produce net interest for the client."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 124.626,
                                "stop": 130.496,
                                "byte_start": 583874,
                                "byte_stop": 607384,
                                "text": "The two petitioners in this case are individuals who regularly purchase and sell real estate."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.496,
                                "stop": 144.395,
                                "byte_start": 607384,
                                "byte_stop": 662973,
                                "text": "One of them made an excrow deposit of about $15,000 that was placed in an IOLTA account for two weeks and the other made a $90,000.00 excrow payment that was held in an IOLTA account for two days."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 144.395,
                                "stop": 172.279,
                                "byte_start": 662973,
                                "byte_stop": 774568,
                                "text": "The parties assumed that the first deposit generated some interest and that the second earned $4.96, but neither petitioner claimed that he could have earned any net interest in a non-IOLTA account, or that the interest earned on his deposit in the IOLTA account actually exceeded the bank charges and other transaction cost that would have been incurred in an attempt to remit any net interest to him."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 172.279,
                                "stop": 177.352,
                                "byte_start": 774568,
                                "byte_stop": 794839,
                                "text": "After discovery, the District Court granted the defendant\u0027s motions for summary judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 177.352,
                                "stop": 196.169,
                                "byte_start": 794839,
                                "byte_stop": 870071,
                                "text": "As a matter of fact, it concluded that in no event can the client depositors make any net returns on the interest acrued in this accounts, and as a matter of law, it concluded that constitutional issue focuses on what the owner has lost not what the government has gained."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 196.169,
                                "stop": 201.771,
                                "byte_start": 870071,
                                "byte_stop": 892537,
                                "text": "Since petitioners had lost nothing there had been no taking without just compensation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 201.771,
                                "stop": 208.747,
                                "byte_start": 892537,
                                "byte_stop": 920435,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit sitting en banc affirm and we granted certiorari."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 208.747,
                                "stop": 224.603,
                                "byte_start": 920435,
                                "byte_stop": 983861,
                                "text": "Like all of the other judges who have participated in this case, we agree with the proposition that just compensation required by the taking clause of the Fifth Amendment is measured by the property owners loss rather by the government\u0027s gain."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 224.603,
                                "stop": 229.332,
                                "byte_start": 983861,
                                "byte_stop": 1002773,
                                "text": "Petitioners\u0027 loss under Washington\u2019s IOLTA rules was zero."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 229.332,
                                "stop": 236.625,
                                "byte_start": 1002773,
                                "byte_stop": 1031926,
                                "text": "As a matter of constitutional law the just compensation that is due for a net loss of zero is zero."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 236.625,
                                "stop": 240.229,
                                "byte_start": 1031926,
                                "byte_stop": 1046346,
                                "text": "Accordingly, we affirm the judgment of the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 240.229,
                                "stop": 251.533,
                                "byte_start": 1046346,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed the dissenting opinion that has joined by the Chief Justice, Justice Kennedy and Justice Thomas; Justice Kennedy has also filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
